# tools/ is downloaded / built by Build-OfflineToolkit.ps1 and Build-OfflineToolkit-Linux.sh
# (Volatility wheels, YARA rules, AVML, Sysinternals, MemProcFS, symbols, …) and is NOT
# committed. The ONE exception is binja/ — the Binary Ninja reverse-engineering tooling
# (Dockerfile, plugins, docs) is part of the repo and IS tracked.
#
# Carved memory regions written to binja/data/ are runtime evidence and stay ignored
# (see binja/data/.gitignore).
*
!.gitignore
!*/
!binja/**
